BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA)--The Wafd Party has withdrawn 
from the committee in charge of preparation for national 
dialogue. 
  AL-WAFD newspaper says in the issue for tomorrow, Thursday, 
that Wafd Party Leader Fu'ad Siraj-al-Din announced his 
withdrawal after a speech he delivered to the committee in its 
(?first) meeting in a People's Assembly Hall this morning, 
Wednesday. 
  The paper says that in his speech, Siraj-al-Din objected to 
the way the committee was formed and to the exclusion of 
political and constitutional reforms from the topics of the 
dialogue. 

